  "text": "# HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 Header Normalization Migration in Envoy\n\nThe HTTP/1.1 to HTTP/2 header translation in Envoy involves three main components: parsing and decoding HTTP/1.1 requests, creating pseudo-headers, and encoding them to HTTP/2 format.\n\n## HTTP/1.1 Parsing and Pseudo-Header Creation\n\nThe HTTP/1.1 codec in `source/common/http/http1/codec_impl.cc` is the primary component that decodes HTTP/1.1 requests and creates HTTP/2 pseudo-headers. Key operations include:\n\n1. **Request Line Parsing**: The `ServerConnectionImpl::onHeadersCompleteBase()` method (line 1186) processes the complete HTTP/1.1 request headers after parsing. It calls `handlePath()` to process the request target.\n\n2. **Pseudo-Header Creation**: In `handlePath()` (line 1100), the codec:\n   - Calls `headers.setMethod(parser_->methodName())` to set the `:method` pseudo-header from the HTTP/1.1 request line\n   - Calls `headers.setPath(absolute_url.pathAndQueryParams())` to set the `:path` pseudo-header\n   - Calls `headers.setScheme(absl::AsciiStrToLower(absolute_url.scheme()))` to set the `:scheme` pseudo-header (with lowercase normalization)\n   - Calls `headers.setHost(absolute_url.hostAndPort())` to set what becomes the `:authority` pseudo-header\n\n3. **HTTP/1.1 Parser**: The `BalsaParser` class in `source/common/http/http1/balsa_parser.cc` provides the `methodName()` method that extracts the HTTP method from the request line. It also validates the HTTP method using `isMethodValid()` and parses the request target into components.\n\n## Header Case Normalization\n\nHeader case normalization (converting to lowercase) occurs in multiple places:\n\n1. **Scheme Normalization**: In `http1/codec_impl.cc` line 1145, the scheme is normalized to lowercase using `absl::AsciiStrToLower(absolute_url.scheme())`.\n\n2. **General Case Handling**: The `conn_manager_utility.cc` file also performs scheme normalization using `absl::AsciiStrToLower()` for consistency.\n\n3. **HTTP/2 Header Encoding**: The `buildHeaders()` method in `http2/codec_impl.cc` (line 250) builds a vector of HTTP/2 headers. The actual wire-format encoding with lowercase header names is handled by the underlying nghttp2 or oghttp2 adapter, which enforces RFC 9113 requirements that all HTTP/2 header field names must be lowercase.\n\n## HTTP/2 Codec and Upgrade Handling\n\nThe HTTP/2 codec in `source/common/http/http2/codec_impl.cc` handles the encoding of headers to HTTP/2 format and special cases like Upgrade requests:\n\n1. **Header Encoding**: The `ConnectionImpl::ClientStreamImpl::encodeHeaders()` method (line 274) is the main entry point for encoding request headers. For upgrade requests, it calls `Http::Utility::transformUpgradeRequestFromH1toH2()` to transform the headers before encoding.\n\n2. **Upgrade Transformation**: The `transformUpgradeRequestFromH1toH2()` function in `source/common/http/utility.cc` (line 1047) handles HTTP Upgrade requests by:\n   - Setting the method to `:method: CONNECT`\n   - Moving the Upgrade header value to the `:protocol` pseudo-header\n   - Removing the Connection and Upgrade headers\n   - Removing Content-Length if it's \"0\"\n\n3. **Response Upgrade Handling**: Similarly, `transformUpgradeResponseFromH1toH2()` (line 1065) transforms HTTP/1.1 upgrade responses for HTTP/2 by:\n   - Converting 101 status to 200\n   - Removing Connection and Upgrade headers\n   - Removing Content-Length if it's \"0\"\n\n## Header Validation and Normalization\n\nThe header validators in `source/extensions/http/header_validators/envoy_default/` provide additional validation and transformation:\n\n1. **HTTP/2 Header Validator** (`http2_header_validator.cc`): Validates pseudo-headers like `:method`, `:path`, `:scheme`, and `:authority` according to RFC 9113. It verifies that header names are all lowercase (line 480).\n\n2. **HTTP/1 Header Validator** (`http1_header_validator.cc`): Handles pseudo-header definitions for HTTP/1.1, mapping the Host header to `:authority` and validating `:method`, `:scheme`, and `:path`.\n\n3. **Upgrade Transformation in Validators**: The header validators also call `transformUpgradeRequestFromH1toH2()` and `transformUpgradeResponseFromH1toH2()` to handle Extended CONNECT upgrades when UHV (Universal Header Validator) is enabled.\n\n## Header Map Implementation\n\nThe header map implementation in `source/common/http/header_map_impl.cc` manages the pseudo-headers and provides methods like `setMethod()`, `setPath()`, `setScheme()`, and `setHost()` that are used throughout the codec pipeline to manipulate HTTP/2 pseudo-headers. The `headers.h` file in `envoy/http/` defines the standard pseudo-header names (Method, Path, Scheme, Host/Authority) that are used consistently across the codebase.\n\n## Connection Management\n\nThe connection manager in `source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc` orchestrates the overall flow, including validation that Host headers are present for HTTP/1.1 requests and ensuring all required pseudo-headers are present for HTTP/2 (as mentioned in line 1222-1227).\n\nThis comprehensive header translation system ensures that HTTP/1.1 requests with arbitrary header casing and formats are properly normalized to HTTP/2 requirements, including lowercase header names, proper pseudo-header usage, and correct handling of special cases like upgrades."
}

